                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.113 Airplanes/96: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-03-12T20:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 12, 1935—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>75. Your 98, February 27, 3 p.m. The Department invites your attention to the
                    requirements of the new regulations governing importation of airplane materials
                    with respect to stamp tax and permit fee and submission of the documents and
                    fees through appropriate diplomatic mission or consular office and points out
                    that compliance therewith would appear, unless an appropriate reservation is
                    made, to imply assent on the part of this Government to the imposition of the
                    fee and the stamp tax on American citizens. It is suggested that the Legation
                    consult with the legations of the other powers concerned and submit
                    recommendations for the consideration of the Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
